reviews.title: Delicious Italian food
reviews.text:
We were received very friendly and got nice spot on the terrace in the historic district of Harlingen. Very atmospheric! Service was super, good explanation about the ingredients and the map. Delicious alcohol-free rosé prosecco drunk and delicious pizza eaten. Not so mega big, but so flavorful and a delicious crust. Fresh ingredients and you can taste them! And then dessert: I love tiramisu, but this one was divinely delicious.....really never had such a delicious tiramisu and didn't fall too heavy on the stomach.... AWESOME!!!
And with that the doppio cappuccino.... blissful! 
Really nothing was less, I will definitely be back soon 🤗

reviews.title: Best pizza in the Netherlands?
reviews.text: Perhaps the best pizza ever eaten here. Not very large size, but crispy bottom and tasty ingredients. Very pleasant service, cordial. Highly recommended!

reviews.title: Good Pizza for this American Family
reviews.text: Lovely restaurant nestled in the historic district of Harlingen. Beautiful indoor and outside seating but plan on having a reservation. We did pizzas to go and they offer a delicious gluten free pizza. All ingredients were high quality and each pizza was made to order.

reviews.title: Go and be surprised!
reviews.text: We were very spontaneous today and without any idea what to expect in this restaurant. And it was a very special and extraordinary meal with great (and also unusual) ingredients. Be sure to go - they won't regret it!

reviews.title: Very nice restaurant and very good food
reviews.text: Along the way we looked for a restaurant in Harlingen and based on the reviews on TA we went here to eat which was very well liked. Cozy restaurant, hugely nice hostess who was very attentive. Very tasty starters, very good pasta and delicious pizzas. The price was very reasonable considering the quality of the food, the temp was also just right. Too bad we live quite a bit from the neighborhood because here we want to eat more often.

reviews.title: As far as we are concerned, San Marino is the Italian gem of Harlingen
reviews.text:
Everything is always right, from the moment you step inside until you leave the cozy building feeling more than satisfied.
The staff are alert, knowledgeable and calm and friendly in approach.
The dishes and the drinks are tasteful and coordinated, are nicely presented and alllless has gone from appetizer to the last pizza tip.
Oh yeah... The salad (with special dressing ) is delicious.

Thank you for a nice king's meal on this King's Day.

reviews.title: Yummie 😋
reviews.text:
Best pizzas in the Netherlands as far as we are concerned!
Not so idiotically big (for us almost always just too big normal, these were perfect). Gorgonzola/pear was delicious; the special Inverno was also a success.
Nice and attentive staff too.

reviews.title: Recommended
reviews.text:
We had a delicious pizza tonight. Friendly and good service. Good price. Cozy atmosphere.
Easy to make a reservation.

reviews.title: Tasty and cozy food
reviews.text: Always difficult to choose from the dishes on the menu here, but actually you can't choose wrong. Really everything is tasty, very tasty and friendly service.

reviews.title: Exceptional service and pizza's
reviews.text: We were greeted with very friendly staff who gave us a table that was a bit separate so our dog could lie down without getting in the way. The service was very pleasant overall, and the food great! We had pizza's (the perfect crust!) with a small side salad (great dressing!). If I lived in Harlingen I would return regularly.

reviews.title: Nice restaurant with great atmosphere
reviews.text: The restaurant was very nice. The food was delicious and the staff very friendly. I would go back anytime.

reviews.title: Delicious
reviews.text: We had a nice time here. The pizzas were excellent and the price was also nice. Nice service and in a nice place in Harlingen

reviews.title: Very nice place, great food!
reviews.text: We were looking for a pizzeria in Harlingen at the last minute and came across it. It was pretty much full, a good sign! It looked very cozy inside. Many staff present and very friendly service. The food was delicious, real Italian food. Highly recommended!

reviews.title: Very good trattoria in a quiet corner of Harlingen
reviews.text:
No weekend restaurant service at my hotel but this splendid restaurant was very close and open on both Saturday and Sunday evenings.

Menu is just as you would expect, Italian with a broad range of pizzas offered but with plenty of pasta based alternatives and a couple of daily specials. Starters were varied and both the salami and cheese platters I tried were generous and very good. A small bowl of green salad was offered between courses as the type of palate cleanser that has sadly all but vanished from France and Italy. 
For mains I had a sea-food pizza on day 1 and a Fregola Frutti di Mare the next (Harlingen is a coastal town) both of which were very good and coffee to finish.

For drinks I stuck to Italian beer and the offered jug of water.

Booking via the website is available but I was accommodated without problem on arrival. Staff were excellent - very professional but always very friendly and helpful without being intrusive.

reviews.title: Long waiting time
reviews.text: We had to wait 2 hours for the food, they forgot the serving. Bleach and wet pizza! Friendly staff! ........................................................

Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

tripContent.title: Orlando: An LGBTQ+ family guide
tripContent.description: "Our family loves going to Orlando—and not just for the theme parks. Yes, we enjoy getting to ride rollercoasters and be transported to another world, but spending time in a colorful, diverse city and the surrounding nature is delightful. We live just over an hour from Orlando, so when we feel the need for good city vibes and to feel welcome in a neighborhood besides our own, Orlando is a fantastic option for us." - Rob Taylor, 2TravelDads.com

reviews.title: Recommended!
reviews.text: Picked up 2 pizzas on the way to the boat. Were tasty and super friendly service by the staff. The pizza came out of the oven at the agreed time and was cut. Recommended!

reviews.title: Surprisingly delicious food!
reviews.text: Had a delicious meal last night! Welcome and a good wine tip: Garganega, fresh and tasty with the Primavera pizza (green asparagus and an egg, mmmm) The dessert was also very tasty! Actually this is more of a restaurant than a pizzaria. Top!

reviews.title: Top value for money & super tasty!
reviews.text: Great service & delicious food. Great value for money! We'll be happy to come back. Make sure to reserve in advance - when we were there all the tables were occupied. Our online reservation worked perfectly!

reviews.title: It is advisable to make a reservation
reviews.text:
Fortunately, we were still able to go without a reservation. Food was fine, game pasta, seasonal dish, etc., staff okay.

Do something about the tour that passes by the wooden wall 😄 can be quite refreshing.

reviews.title: Delicious pizzas! Highly recommended
reviews.text: We picked up food here, which is a bit more relaxing with young children. We called in advance and everything was ready at the agreed time. The food was really fantastic! Not standard average pizzas, but really a few steps better in terms of quality. Really freshly baked with fresh ingredients and you can taste it! Highly recommended and we will definitely eat in the restaurant again.

reviews.title: An excellent address
reviews.text:
Excellent Italian restaurant.
We have been visiting this establishment for several years.
Everything is always perfect. Very pleasant and friendly staff. The dishes are based on fresh produce. This evening I made a mistake on the pizza I ordered. I was very quickly served a new pizza which was not charged for. Thank you very much for this attention. See you soon, we will come back with great pleasure.

reviews.title: Well you had your chance...
reviews.text:
I won't be returning, but not because of the food, anyone can have a bad day. I'm from Italy and  the hospitality industry. But the attitude of one staff member who at each moment tried to have the last say and made us feel as if we were the ones at fault. 
And it was quite chilly but we were not going to complain, we just put our coats on. I will be using this case with my students at the Hotel school I teach.

reviews.title: Delicious Pizza
reviews.text: Delicious pizza at San Marino. Friendly service and attentive staff. Busy on a Saturday night, glad I made a reservation.

reviews.title: Delicious authentic Italian food
reviews.text: You know when you've found a good restaurant when the staff truly welcome you. And then to find an authentic roman carbonara with guancale and no cream: tremendous. Thoroughly recommended.

reviews.title: Good food, nice atmosphere
reviews.text: A nice and cosy place for dinner. We had the pizzas which were fresh and tasty. Staff is friendly and quick.

reviews.title: Brilliant Italian
reviews.text: Had an absolutely awesome meal here tonight while spending the night in Harlingen. Fantastic pizzas, lively olives and gorgeous bruschetta. I wish I had an Italian as good as this near to me. Great service too.

reviews.title: Starving tourists find gem of an eating place!
reviews.text:
We stumbled upon Piazzeria San Marino, Harlingen, by chance whilst looking for food one evening. An hotelier recommended it to us.
The staff recognised our tiredness and hunger and got to work immediately offering lovely wine to our taste and the best pizza we have eaten and we are aged 73 and 67!
The ambience was very appropriate for this kind of restaurant - happy, friendly and professional.  
We immediately relaxed and the stresses of an overlong journed due to big traffic hold ups coming from Norway soon dissipated. A place to return to!

reviews.title: Reunion with our family as we are from Canada
reviews.text: Relaxing ,fresh decor and delicious Italian food.the wine was very nice too and not to expensive ,I liked starting outside as the seating is always nice

photo.caption: Yummy food! When your traveling and you need to taste Italian food you will not be disappointed

reviews.title: Yummy yummy
reviews.text: We just had dinner at San Marino. Yummy pizza and calzone. Friendly staff. You know it has to be good food when the place fills up with locals. Inexpensive and delicious. Highly recommended. Incredible find in a cute seaside village.

reviews.title: Recommended!
reviews.text: Delicious pizza and very friendly staff. Nice restaurant with very nice decor. Reservations recommended.

reviews.title: Unique pizza and pasta for good value
reviews.text: Friends of mine in Friesland took me to this restaurant in Harlingen during a recent visit, and it was a wonderful meal.  The menu is varied, with several pages of pizza varieties, which include delicious vegetarian choices, and you can choose your own toppings.  The owners are the chefs hard at work in the kitchen, and all of the food is fresh and high quality.  They respond to special requests and dietary requirements, and the wait staff is professional and attentive. The salad that comes with the meal was very good, and the house dressing s a closely guarded secret of herbs, oil and vinegar.  The wine and beverages were also well represented on the menu, with good value for main courses.  Most pizzas are between 8.50 to 11.50 Euro, and are large and filling for the price.  We sat outside at a patio table in the quiet picturesque street.  The only drawback is that the smoking area is right outside the front entrance, close to the patio tables, so that the smoke drifted across our table.   I defnitely recommend this restaurant for a quality meal at a good price.
